<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-18T13:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-18T13:30:00-05:00" n="873" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d873">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">833.5151/548: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reed</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-18T15:00:00-03:30">October 18, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 18—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. According to the Bank of the Republic import quotas of controlled
                            foreign exchange for the month of October have just been granted to 13
                            countries excluding the United States. Quotas total 301,500 pounds of
                            which 100,000 are for Great Britain and 100,000 for Germany.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>